We  talked last week about a typo in Lyft Inc.=E2=80=99s fourth-quarter ear=
nings release. On the second page of the release, under =E2=80=9CFY=E2=80=
=9924 Directional Commentary,=E2=80=9D Lyft said that it expected its adjus=
ted Ebitda margin to expand by =E2=80=9Capproximately 500 basis points year=
-over-year.=E2=80=9D Later, Lyft put out a correction saying that was actua=
lly=C2=A050=C2=A0basis points. The stock rallied hard on the wrong number, =
then fell a bit on the right one. =E2=80=9CMy bad,=E2=80=9D  said Lyft=E2=
=80=99s chief executive officer, but also: =E2=80=9CIt was one zero in a pr=
ess release.=E2=80=9D I mean, honestly, fair.
Could be worse! Mister Car Wash Inc. put out its fourth-quarter earnings re=
lease at 4:12 p.m. yesterday. Its =E2=80=9CFiscal 2024 Outlook=E2=80=9D inc=
ludes comparable-store sales growth of -0.5% to 2.5%. Later in the evening,=
 Mister Car Wash put out a revised earnings release=C2=A0to =E2=80=9Ccorrec=
t a clerical error,=E2=80=9D changing that guidance to +0.5% to 2.5%. =E2=
=80=9CIt was one minus sign in a press release,=E2=80=9D I suppose, but if =
you work in finance you want to avoid extraneous minus signs? If you are go=
ing to sprinkle characters at random into your press releases, zeros are pr=
etty good ones to sprinkle.=C2=A0Minus signs are bad!
Planet Fitness Inc. put out its fourth-quarter earnings release at 6:31 a.m=
. today. Its =E2=80=9C2024 Outlook=E2=80=9D includes =E2=80=9Csystem-wide s=
ame store sales [growth] in the high single-digit percentage range.=E2=80=
=9D Later this morning, it put out a revised earnings release=C2=A0to =E2=
=80=9Ccorrect a clerical error,=E2=80=9D changing that guidance to 5% to 6%=
, which I suppose would be mid single-digits. I guess that one=E2=80=99s no=
t really a typo. Six is in the top half of the single digits? I dunno.
Anyway Mister Car Wash=E2=80=99s and Planet Fitness=E2=80=99=C2=A0typos did=
n=E2=80=99t cause huge volumes of volatile trading, as Lyft=E2=80=99s appar=
ently did.
  [5]
 I don=E2=80=99t think there=E2=80=99s anything you really could have done =
with this information, but it is nice that Lyft is not alone I guess.

