<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a senior partner at Goldman Sachs G=
roup Inc., you are not really in it for the money. Oh, I mean, you=E2=80=99=
re in it for the money =E2=80=94=C2=A0you get paid a lot, and you probably =
have an expensive lifestyle =E2=80=94=C2=A0but you have already made a lot =
of money, you have marketable skills, you can afford to quit, and the money=
 is not top of mind.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">No, if you are a senior partner at Goldman, yo=
u are in it for the=C2=A0<em>committees</em>. You have devoted much of your=
 career to Goldman, and what you care about is your standing among the Gold=
man partnership, the respect that you get within the firm. And the surest i=
ndicator of that standing is what committees you are on. Ideally you=E2=80=
=99d be on the management committee; that=E2=80=99s the best committee, and=
 being on that means that you are in the inner circle of senior partners. B=
ut if you can=E2=80=99t be on the management committee, there are some othe=
r good committees, and you=E2=80=99d like to at least be on them.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And there are very fine-grained forms of jealo=
usy here. If you are the co-head of some important business, and you are no=
t on a committee, and the other co-head of that business=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0<=
/em>on that committee, that is a mortal insult. <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34440618.286382/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2Nvb=
nRlbnQvOWIxMDMwN2ItYjUzYi00MWM1LTgxODItMmFkM2EzYmVjZTJk/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB3b78c77d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> The Financial Times reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Two of Goldman Sachs=E2=80=99 top investment b=
ankers have threatened to quit after being excluded from a new operating co=
mmittee established under chief executive David Solomon, according to peopl=
e familiar with the matter.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mark Sorrell, the London-based co-head of merg=
ers and acquisitions and son of advertising executive Sir Martin Sorrell, a=
nd Gonzalo Garcia, co-head of European investment banking, have told Goldma=
n they may leave after being excluded from the committee, the people said.=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Their respective co-heads =E2=80=94 Stephan Fe=
ldgoise in mergers and acquisitions and Anthony Gutman in European investme=
nt banking =E2=80=94 have been included in the committee, which has about a=
 dozen members. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The source of the latest unrest is two new ope=
rating committees for investment banking and trading established by Solomon=
 this year. They sit below Goldman=E2=80=99s top-tier management committee.=
=C2=A0Both Sorrell and Garcia were left out of the investment banking commi=
ttee, the people said. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Conceived as a way to promote a new generation=
 of leaders at Goldman and to streamline decision making, the new committee=
s have ruffled feathers internally about who was in or out, the people said=
. Conspicuously absent from the committee in investment banking was anyone =
from Goldman=E2=80=99s equity capital markets and real estate businesses.=
=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Spectacular stuff, the most Goldman of all sto=
ries. Disclosure: I used to work at Goldman, and while=C2=A0I was very very=
 far from being committee material, this story resonates with me. If you wo=
rk at Goldman and you turn to your colleague and say =E2=80=9Cmy rival was =
just put on committee and I was not, I think I have to quit,=E2=80=9D your =
colleague will nod solemnly and say =E2=80=9Cyes of course, we=E2=80=99ll m=
iss you, but you=E2=80=99ve got to have principles.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Do you think they=E2=80=99ll quit? Do you thin=
k the threat will get them put on the committees? Also, if you are the CEO =
of Goldman you have all sorts of opportunities to use committees tactically=
. Are you worried that too many partners are leaving? Create some new commi=
ttees and put lots of partners on them; that will make them feel good. Do y=
ou=C2=A0<em>want=C2=A0</em>more disfavored partners to leave? Create some n=
ew committees and leave those partners off; they=E2=80=99ll quit in five mi=
nutes.=C2=A0</p>
